<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old man who drove his car into two men outside a bar, killing one of 
them, was sentenced Thursday to 15 years to life in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
Ruben Guzman Valle of Escondido also was ordered to pay $6,000 in funeral 
expenses to the family of Alfredo Chavez Sandoval, 33, who watched the 
sentencing by San Diego Superior Court Judge William Mudd. 
</P>
<P>
Guzman pleaded guilty to second-degree murder in the March 20 incident outside 
a Southeast San Diego bar. He earlier had been involved in a dispute with the 
two men over a woman inside the bar. 
</P>
<P>
Guzman's attorney, Wayne Gomez, told the judge the defendant had no 
recollection of what had occurred that night. 
</P>
<P>
Although Guzman had been drinking and had cocaine in his system, the judge 
remarked that the defendant probably knew what was happening. "All of this over 
some misunderstanding in a bar," Mudd said. 
</P>
<P>
Injured in the same incident was Cirenio Samano, 34, who suffered a broken leg, 
but did not appear at the sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
Before his arrest, Guzman was a cook at a Rancho Bernardo seafood restaurant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
