<HEADLINE>
<P>
FUROR OVER NEW LITERATURE TEXTBOOKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The debate in Yucaipa over the "Impressions" reading series brings to mind 
another book that has long been banned in our public schools. 
</P>
<P>
It is a compilation of stories containing numerous descriptions of murder, 
torture, genocide, rape, bestiality, adultery, incest, homosexuality, group sex 
and devil worship. Ironically, it is still found in most church-run schools. It 
is, of course, the Bible. 
</P>
<P>
STEVE MILLS 
</P>
