<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 3 MAY HAVE TO PAY POLICE FOR FAKING 
DISAPPEARANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rialto police said Thursday they are considering making three women who faked 
their own disappearance pay for the $10,000 investigation into what police 
feared was a bloody kidnaping. 
</P>
<P>
"Why should the taxpayers be duped for a harebrained idea like this?" asked 
Rialto Police Capt. Phil Greek. 
</P>
<P>
He said an investigation of the hoax by Suzanne Ballinger, 38, her 17-year-old 
daughter, Sherry Richards, and Sherry's friend, Laura Fleming, 18, cost the 
Police Department about $10,000. Greek said he has asked the city attorney of 
Rialto to look into possibly billing the women. 
</P>
<P>
The three turned up unharmed in Ogden, Utah, Wednesday night, nearly a week 
after they abandoned a blood-stained car in North Hollywood, Greek said. As for 
the motive for the hoax, Greek said Ballinger was seeking sympathy from family 
members. He said she was frustrated with driving two hours to work in Van Nuys 
and was upset about her financial situation. 
</P>
<P>
The department does not plan to file criminal charges against the women. 
</P>
