<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MENENDEZ BROTHERS APPEAL TO HIGH COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Beverly Hills brothers accused of the shotgun murders of their parents for 
a $14-million inheritance have asked the California Supreme Court to block 
prosecutors from using a tape of an alleged confession. 
</P>
<P>
Erik Menendez, 19, and Joseph Lyle Menendez, 22, petitioned the high court on 
Wednesday to overturn an appeals court decision permitting prosecutors to take 
possession of a tape made by the brothers' therapist after the slayings of Jose 
and Mary Menendez in their home on Aug. 20 last year. 
</P>
<P>
If the Supreme Court declines to keep prosecutors from using the tape, defense 
lawyers said they will challenge its use as evidence on other grounds. 
</P>
<P>
The brothers, who deny killing their parents, are being held without bail 
pending a preliminary hearing Oct. 22. 
</P>
