<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
AIR TRAVELERS URGED TO ARRIVE EARLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFFREY A. PERLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Travelers planning to use John Wayne Airport this Labor Day weekend were urged 
Thursday to arrive as early as possible because of the holiday crowds, airport 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Besides Thanksgiving and New Year's, the Labor Day weekend always produces one 
of the biggest jams of the year at the airport. 
</P>
<P>
Last year's count came to 42,208 passengers for the three-day weekend, with a 
similar number expected this year, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Officials urged travelers to arrive at least two hours before their their 
flight departures and to arrange to be dropped off rather than drive or leave 
their cars in the airport parking garage. 
</P>
<P>
Moving around the airport is expected to be a little easier now, however, 
because a new ramp leads traffic leaving the airport directly onto the 
northbound Costa Mesa Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
The new $62-million Thomas F. Riley Terminal is scheduled to open on Sept. 16, 
after a Sept. 8 open house. JEFFREY A. PERLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
