ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: COMPCARE SELECTS NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James P. Carmany has been named president and chief executive of Comprehensive 
Care Corp. by a new board of directors that recently won control of the firm in 
a proxy fight. 
</P>
<P>
Carmany, of Laguna Niguel, was a former vice president of the chemical 
dependency treatment firm and a leader of the dissident group that won the 
proxy battle. He has promised to improve the finances of the company, which 
lost $61.2 million for its fiscal year ended May 31. CompCare also named Donald 
G. Simpson, also a former CompCare officer, executive vice president and chief 
operating officer. 
