<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE MAY PRODUCE RECORD PISTACHIO CROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California, the main source of U.S. pistachios, is producing a record crop of 
the nuts this year, the Agriculture Department said. 
</P>
<P>
Production was estimated at 115 million pounds, an in-shell weight, almost 
triple last year's harvest and 22% more than the previous record of 94 million 
pounds in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
