<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAY AREA ROASTERS PLAN A NEW BLEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OAKLAND 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a deal that unites the area's most venerable gourmet coffee roasters, 
Peerless Coffee of Oakland plans to buy bankrupt United Coffee Corp. of San 
Francisco for $3 million. 
</P>
<P>
The deal is expected to be completed by Sept. 20, but the purchase price needs 
approval from the U.S. Bankruptcy Court in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
The sale should help United Coffee pay off its listed $4.1-million debt to 
creditors. The company owes $2 million to Wells Fargo Bank alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
