The Times also incorrectly reported that The Wellington Group is part of 
Pentagon Investment Group, a real estate consortium. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the story said the corporation was co-owner of Toluca Court apartments, a 
48-unit building taken over by the state as part of the court action. Roger L. 
Merwin, a Wellington Group vice president, said Wellington never owned a share 
of the building. Mark Harman, an attorney for the state, said state 
investigators believe that Wellington was a co-owner. 
