<TEXT>
<P>
China trounced the United States, and the Soviet Union beat Cuba today in the 
semifinals of the 11th World Women's Volleyball Championships. 
</P>
<P>
China is a five-time defending world champion, and the Soviets are the Olympic 
champions. They play for the title Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
China defeated the United States, 15-7, 15-8, 15-7, and the Soviets downed 
Cuba, 17-15, 15-7, 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
China, led by veteran star Lang Ping, blanked the United States in only one 
hour, as the Americans gave up 15 points on mistakes. 
</P>
<P>
The United States will play Cuba on Saturday for third place. 
